description: Creates a service. A service is any software application that can run on instances containers, or serverless functions within an account or virtual private cloud (VPC). For more information, see Services in the Amazon VPC Lattice User Guide.

parameters.name: authType
parameters.description: The type of IAM policy. NONE: The resource does not use an IAM policy. This is the default. AWS_IAM: The resource uses an IAM policy. When this type is used, auth is enabled and an auth policy is required.

parameters.name: clientToken
parameters.description: A unique, case-sensitive identifier that you provide to ensure the idempotency of the request. If you retry a request that completed successfully using the same client token and parameters, the retry succeeds without performing any actions. If the parameters aren't identical, the retry fails. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the service. The name must be unique within the account. The valid characters are a-z, 0-9, and hyphens (-). You can't use a hyphen as the first or last character, or immediately after another hyphen.

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: The tags for the service. (string) --- The key of the tag. Constraints: Tag keys are case-sensitive and accept a maximum of 128 Unicode characters. Valid characters are Unicode letters, digits, white space, and any of the following symbols: _ . : / = + - @ May not begin with aws:. (string) --- The value of the tag. Constraints: Tag values are case-sensitive and accept a maximum of 256 Unicode characters. : / = + - @

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the service.

nested_items.name: certificateArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the certificate.

nested_items.name: customDomainName
nested_items.description: The custom domain name of the service.

nested_items.name: domainName
nested_items.description: The domain name of the service.

nested_items.name: hostedZoneId
nested_items.description: The ID of the hosted zone.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status. If the status is CREATE_FAILED, you must delete and recreate the service.
